HEADWORD: Inextirpable
<hw>In`ex*tir"pa*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>inexstirpabilis</ets>: cf. F. <ets>inextirpable</ets>. See
<er>In-</er> not, and <er>Extirpate</er>.]</ety> <def>Not capable of
being extirpated or rooted out; ineradicable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

